<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by morodullin on 08-14-2001 01:15 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Simply put, Velk's lab is too easy.

I like it. I take advantage of it. But I'm honest enough to admit it's too easy.

My last upper spider camp was three hours long. I never used CH. I used a dozen or so Celestial Elixirs. That's it. Three hours, a dozen mediocre heals. 

My concern is this: How many clerics come in here at 50ish, and level their butts of by sleeping through camps where they don't ever have to heal? How much skill are these players missing out on? What happens when some day they end up getting invited to HS and have to find a way to save the group when the puller comes back with 6 mobs (after taking 4 HTs on the pull)?

Not gonna be my problem, because I am never in a group with another cleric, and I mostly raid with my guild and all our clerics know their jobs well. But my friends and guildmates have been complaining more often lately that they have a bad cleric that can't seem to keep their enchanter alive...These complaints have become more and more frequent in the last few weeks.

Maybe it's not the ONLY fault of Velk's lab, but it cannot be a good thing when clerics let their healing skills atrophy by spending weeks in camps that don't keep their skills honed...

I hope verant does something to make this zone risk/reward comparable to sebilis. Givin the easy access to ports and bind spots, I would say the zone could even survive being a bit harder risk/reward than sebilis, just to be fair.

And yes, I say this despite the fact I myself take advantage of this zone (level 60 before they made it so easy, but I come here for gems and farmable loot drops).

Morodullin Brellfury
Concerned Saint of Brell </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
